  <code>
    <?xml version="1.0"?>
    <html>
      <head>
        <title>Test Case for libxml2 Function Call Path</title>
      </head>
      <body>
        <h1>Test Case for libxml2 Function Call Path</h1>

        <p>This test case is designed to execute the following function call path in the libxml2 project:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><code>streamFile</code></li>
          <li><code>xmlTextReaderRead</code></li>
          <li><code>xmlParseChunk</code></li>
          <li><code>xmlSAX2ResolveEntity</code></li>
          <li><code>xmlBuildURISafe</code></li>
          <li><code>xmlSaveUri</code></li>
        </ol>
      </body>
    </html>
  </code>

  <p>The following code will be used to execute the test case:</p>

  <code>
    #include <stdio.h>
    #include <stdlib.h>
    #include <string.h>
    #include <libxml/parser.h>

    int main() {
      // Create a new XML reader
      xmlTextReaderPtr reader = xmlReaderForFile("test.xml", NULL, 0);

      // Read the XML file
      int result = xmlTextReaderRead(reader);

      // Check if the XML file was read successfully
      if (result == 1) {
        // Parse the XML file
        xmlParserCtxtPtr ctxt = xmlNewParserCtxt();
        xmlParseChunk(ctxt, reader->input->cur, reader->input->length, 0);

        // Resolve the external entities
        xmlSAX2ResolveEntity(ctxt, NULL, NULL);

        // Build the URI safe string
        char *uri = xmlBuildURISafe(NULL, NULL, NULL);

        // Save the URI to a file
        xmlSaveUri(uri);

        // Free the memory
        xmlFreeParserCtxt(ctxt);
        xmlFreeTextReader(reader);
        xmlFree(uri);
      } else {
        // Print an error message
        fprintf(stderr, "Error: Unable to read the XML file.\n");
      }

      return 0;
    }
  </code>

